    <div class="content">
        <div class="ttypography"><p>Hello, Codefoolers!</p><p>We, <a class="rated-user user-orange" href="/profile/AlperenT" title="Master AlperenT">AlperenT</a>, <a class="rated-user user-red" href="/profile/Ari" title="International Grandmaster Ari">Ari</a>, <a class="rated-user user-violet" href="/profile/ToxicPie9" title="Candidate Master ToxicPie9">ToxicPie9</a>, <a class="rated-user user-orange" href="/profile/flamestorm" title="International Master flamestorm">flamestorm</a>, <a class="rated-user user-red" href="/profile/prvocislo" title="Grandmaster prvocislo">prvocislo</a>, <a class="rated-user user-orange" href="/profile/temporary1" title="International Master temporary1">temporary1</a>, and <a class="rated-user user-orange" href="/profile/willy108" title="Master willy108">willy108</a> would like to invite everyone on Codeforces to <a href="/contest/2214" title="April Fools Day Contest 2026">April Fools Day Contest 2026</a>! The 14th April Fools Day Contest will take place on <a class="contest-time" contestid="2214" href="https://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/fixedtime.html?day=1&amp;month=4&amp;year=2026&amp;hour=17&amp;min=35&amp;sec=0&amp;p1=166"><span class="format-time-with-dow">Apr/01/2026 17:35 (Moscow time)</span></a>. This is a joke competition in which solving the problem is often easier than figuring out what the actual task is.</p><p>In this round, you will be given $$$n$$$ problems where $$$n$$$ is the number of different AI models I used today and <strong>2</strong> hours to solve them. The contest will use extended ICPC rules (no hacks, the standings are decided by the number of solved problems and penalty time earned on them). You can submit solutions in any language allowed by Codeforces, unless the problem says otherwise. </p><p>There will be at least one non-interactive problem. In case you do not care about those problems, <a href="https://codeforces.com/blog/entry/45307">here</a> is the guide for interactive problems.</p><p>Please note that the round is <strong>unrated</strong> and that the penalty for a <strong>wrong submission</strong> is <strong>10</strong> minutes. Furthermore, similar to other contests, it is not allowed to use AI help unless permitted in <a href="https://codeforces.com/blog/entry/133941">this</a> blog.</p><p>To get an idea of what the contest will look like, you can check out the contests of the past years: <a href="https://codeforces.com/contest/171">2012</a>, <a href="https://codeforces.com/contest/290">2013</a>, <a href="https://codeforces.com/contest/409">2014</a>, <a href="https://codeforces.com/contest/656">2016</a>, <a href="https://codeforces.com/contest/784">2017</a>, <a href="https://codeforces.com/contest/952">2018</a>, <a href="https://codeforces.com/contest/1145">2019</a>, <a href="https://codeforces.com/contest/1331">2020</a>, <a href="https://codeforces.com/contest/1505">2021</a>, <a href="https://codeforces.com/contest/1663">2022</a>, <a href="https://codeforces.com/contest/1812">2023</a>, <a href="https://codeforces.com/contest/1952">2024</a>, <a href="https://codeforces.com/contest/2095">2025</a>, <a>2026</a>. (Does anyone ever click these anyway, why do I have to keep adding them each year?)</p><p>Thanks to our precious testers:</p><p>ChatGPT, Gemini, Claude, Grok, DeepSeek, and a few others who preferred to remain anonymous.</p><p>It is, without a doubt, the least enjoyable part of April Fools for us to respond to clarification requests with funny responses. It is certainly not the main motivator for us to prepare these contests in the first place. Therefore, please refrain from continuing this tradition.</p><p>Good luck, and <strong>have fun</strong>!</p><p>Update 1:</p><p><a href="https://codeforces.com/blog/entry/152573">Editorial</a> is released!</p><p>Update 2:</p><p>Congratulations to the winners:</p> <ol>   <li><a class="rated-user user-legendary" href="/profile/ksun48" title="Legendary Grandmaster ksun48"><span class="legendary-user-first-letter">k</span>sun48</a></li>   <li><a class="rated-user user-red" href="/profile/SeptaCube" title="Grandmaster SeptaCube">SeptaCube</a></li>   <li><a class="rated-user user-red" href="/profile/pwild" title="Grandmaster pwild">pwild</a></li>   <li><a class="rated-user user-orange" href="/profile/0x0c5cbae8" title="International Master 0x0c5cbae8">0x0c5cbae8</a></li>   <li><a class="rated-user user-orange" href="/profile/ishmeal" title="Master ishmeal">ishmeal</a></li> </ol><p>And the first solves on each problem (after blatant cheaters):</p> <ul>   <li>A: <a class="rated-user user-violet" href="/profile/shash4321" title="Candidate Master shash4321">shash4321</a> — 0 minutes</li>   <li>B: <a class="rated-user user-legendary" href="/profile/ksun48" title="Legendary Grandmaster ksun48"><span class="legendary-user-first-letter">k</span>sun48</a> — 0 minutes</li>   <li>C: <a class="rated-user user-red" href="/profile/jdurie" title="International Grandmaster jdurie">jdurie</a> — 4 minutes</li>   <li>D: <a class="rated-user user-blue" href="/profile/thespace" title="Expert thespace">thespace</a> — 3 minutes</li>   <li>E: <a class="rated-user user-legendary" href="/profile/ksun48" title="Legendary Grandmaster ksun48"><span class="legendary-user-first-letter">k</span>sun48</a> — 4 minutes</li>   <li>F: <a class="rated-user user-red" href="/profile/SeptaCube" title="Grandmaster SeptaCube">SeptaCube</a> — 13 minutes</li>   <li>G: <a class="rated-user user-red" href="/profile/bronze_coder" title="Grandmaster bronze_coder">bronze_coder</a> — 51 minutes</li>   <li>H: <a class="rated-user user-blue" href="/profile/circle977" title="Expert circle977">circle977</a> — 1 minutes</li>   <li>I: <a class="rated-user user-blue" href="/profile/Egg_Knight" title="Expert Egg_Knight">Egg_Knight</a> — 33 minutes</li>   <li>J: <a class="rated-user user-blue" href="/profile/Nagerhide" title="Expert Nagerhide">Nagerhide</a> — 11 minutes</li> </ul></div>

